      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WATCH AND SEE (1) scored (17.06) last time out at this track adding to an already respectable career. Has a strong record at this journey including three wins. Winner at his latest appearance in one of the quickest times on the card. Flying at the moment and expecting another big run. CERISE (8) bolted in last time, scoring by 2.5 lengths in slick time (16.75) to take a TG1-4W in a new PB this course and distance. Harder here but will be in this for a long way. WHY SHOULD SHE (2) filled a minor placing last start at Murray Bridge behind One Margarita (16.99) in a Grade 6. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Can measure up. WOW HIS NORM (6) has claims fresh from a recent placing.",
